OL,6,FAs Hughes made his way back through
OL,7,Fthe house, he stole the woman's purse
OL,8,Fwhich contained #100 cash and a bank
OL,9,Fcard.
OL,11,FHe later returned to the address and
OL,12,Fwas confronted by the victim and her
OL,13,Fdaughter about the stolen items.
OL,15,FHughes denied stealing the purse, but
OL,16,Ftook #100 out of his pocket and gave
OL,17,Fit to the victim.
OL,19,FWhen pressed further on the missing
OL,20,Fpurse and bank card, Hughes simply
OL,21,Fwalked away.
